I just want to remind you all that Tex is lying about being intersex.
As >>22534879 points out, there are many different kinds of intersexuality. And they have very different physical symptoms.
Texanon claims to not know what kind of intersexuality he has. This is legitimately preposterous.
We know that Tex has intersex genitalia, meaning that he has a 'severe' (for lack of a better word) form of intersexuality. This contrasts with some chromosomal forms of intersexuality which have little to no effect on a person's body, and can go undiscovered for life. Doctors would have noticed Tex's genitalia while he was in the womb. With Tex's parents' permission, doctors would have been able to determine exactly what kind of intersexuality Tex had - if not before birth, then soon after. It is highly likely that Tex's parents would have given permission for these tests because it is medically important information. Different kinds of intersexuality have a profound effect on the body's interaction with certain medications, risks of medical conditions, cancers, etc. It is vital for a parent to know these things.
But okay. Maybe Tex's parents didn't get these tests done, or they did, but they never told Tex the results, leaving him unsure. It doesn't matter, because Tex has been hospitalised multiple times in his life, including as an independent adult. If Texanon couldn't tell the doctors what kind of intersexuality he has, they would have tested him immediately upon entry and told him the results. Again, this is vital medical information, like doing a blood test, there's no way to get around it.

Can you imagine having a condition as major as intersexuality - one which places you apart from 99% of society - and not taking any steps to understand your situation? Living in ignorance about the workings of your own body? Knowing that you are neither male nor female, but not taking any steps to figure out what you are instead? It is ridiculous.

One of the fastest things I did, that I never hear any other voice teacher talk about, is this:

>first, don't be tone deaf, very important
>find an instrument, any instrument, doesn't matter.
>hit a note on that instrument, one that's in the upper 50% of your range, but not into falsetto
>match that pitch with your voice, keep playing the note, and keep singing it.
>now, funk around with your voice, do big dog small dog, whisper sirens, etc, WHILE singing this note.
>because you're pitch-matching, the only thing you can do to modify your voice is to alter your resonance through various means. It makes it easier to feel what muscles do what aside from pitch.

honestly all this "big dog, small dog" "larynx this, larynx that"

here's the EZ way of doing it:
>download voicepitchmonitor
>do an "aaaaaaaaahh" and try to move the bar on the app up and down
>get the hang of how to move it up and down
>do "aaaaaah" at A3 and learn to hold it there
>expand from "aaah" to "hiiii-haaaa.hoooo-heee" still at A3
>start talking (super monotone, you will sound like a robot) at A3, one word at a time, it will sound stupid
>keep doing this until it's easy and no longer difficult to do the robospeak at A3
>bind the words together, still kind of monotone-ish
>start saying words and common phrases in a less monotone way, incorprating glissando (google)
>keep doing this
>boom there you go, now you have a decently convincable girlvoice without all the fucking meme shit that "voice coaches" on discord make you do.
